---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import IndexGrid from "../components/IndexGrid.astro";
import LinkBox from "../components/LinkBox.astro";
---

<BaseLayout description="Index" width="medium">
  <h1>λ</h1>

  <p id="homepage-quote" style="text-align: center"></p>
  <script is:inline>
    var quotes = [
      {
        text: "\u201cThat is well said,\u201d Candide replied, \u201cbut we must cultivate our garden.\u201d",
        citation: "<em>Candide<\/em>, Voltaire (trans. Peter Constantine)",
      },
      {
        text: "Homo sum, humani nihil a me alienum puto.",
        citation: "<em>Heauton Timorumenos<\/em>, Terence",
      },
      {
        text: "Horas non numero nisi serenas.",
        citation: "Inscription of a Venetian sundial",
      },
      {
        text: "Non fui, fui, non sum, non curo.",
        citation: "Customary Epicurean epitaph",
      },
      {
        text: "Everything is strange, in this world. Wherever you look, strangeness blooms.",
        citation: "<em>Moonbound</em>, Robin Sloan",
      },
      {
        text: "Do not lose time on daily trivialities. Do not dwell on petty detail. For all of these things melt away and drift apart within the obscure traffic of time. Live well and live broadly. You are alive and living now. Now is the envy of all of the dead.",
        citation: "<em>World of Tomorrow</em>, Don Hertzfeldt",
      },
      {
        text: "The day of judgment is either approaching, or it is not. If it is not, there is no cause for an adjournment; if it is, I choose to be found doing my duty. I wish therefore that candles may be brought.",
        citation:
          "A member of the Connecticut Governor's council during New England's Dark Day of 1780",
      },
      {
        text: "Ars longa, vita brevis",
        citation: "Traditional Latin aphorism",
      },
    ];
    var q = quotes[Math.floor(Math.random() * quotes.length)];
    document.getElementById("homepage-quote").innerHTML =
      "<em>" + q.text + "<\/em> \u2014 " + q.citation;
  </script>

  <p>
    Hi, I'm Russell, a writer and programmer in the Bay Area. I've been writing
    essays, newsletters, and evergreen notes on this little site for six years
    (!) now, totaling more than a quarter million words. Originally inspired by
    Robin Sloan's <a
      href="https://www.robinsloan.com/special/year-of-the-meteor/"
      ><em>Year of the Meteor</em></a
    > newsletter, you'll find all kinds of topics within, including among others:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li>
      <em
        >The trials and travails of writing (and rewriting, and rewriting...) a
        novel(s).</em
      >
    </li>
    <li>
      <em
        >Musings on cultural evolution, memory, cognition, consciousness, and
        neurodiversity.</em
      >
    </li>
    <li>
      <em
        >Technical content of interest to professional software engineers and
        particularly engaged amateurs.</em
      >
    </li>
    <li>
      <em
        >Literary criticism, which is to say, music, book, and film
        recommendations.</em
      >
    </li>
  </ul>

