  <h2 class="cv">CV</h2>

  <p>
    Professionally, I am a software engineer (that was probably obvious from
    saying I'm a programmer in the Bay Area, eh?). I am shortly joining <a
      href="https://www.vanta.com/">Vanta</a
    > and was formerly a product engineer at <a href="https://www.descript.com"
      >Descript</a
    > and <a href="https://asana.com/">Asana</a>. As you probably assumed, my
    opinions here are my own and don't reflect the views of my current, future,
    or former employers.
  </p>

  <p>
    I have a bachelor's degree in computer science & mathematics from the <a
      href="https://www.ubc.ca/">University of British Columbia</a
    >. I live in San Francisco with <a href="http://sherryyuan.me"
      >my wife Sherry</a
    > and our small canine companion Rooibos.
  </p>

  <h2>Colophon</h2>

  <p>
    This site is built with <a href="https://astro.build">Astro</a>. The body
    text is <a href="https://practicaltypography.com/charter.html">Charter</a> (falling
    back on the <a
      href="https://github.com/system-fonts/modern-font-stacks#transitional"
      >Transitional fonts</a
    > from <a href="https://modernfontstacks.com">Modern Font Stacks</a>).
    Monospace text is <a href="https://www.brailleinstitute.org/freefont/"
      >Atkinson Hyperlegible Mono</a
    >. The color palette is primarily from Matthew Howell's <a
      href="https://www.reasonable.work/colors/">Reasonable Colors</a
    > and the icons are from <a href="https://heroicons.com/">heroicons</a>. The
    site is served via <a href="https://workers.cloudflare.com"
      >Cloudflare Workers</a
    >. You can see the full source on <a
      href="https://github.com/rwblickhan/astro-rwblickhan.org">Github</a
    >.
  </p>

  <p>
    I heavily use the Greek lambda as a personal symbol because I played too
    much <em>Half-Life 2</em> as a child and because I had a brief, torrid love affair
    with the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lambda_calculus"
      >lambda calculus</a
    > as a university student.
  </p>

